output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of all subjects now working in Education who studied in each region 5 years after graduation, male and female First degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
output.maptext: For First degree graduates of all subjects'' in the ''Education'' industry ''5'' years after graduation, the region that saw the highest number of students studying there was ''South East''. The region with the lowest number of students studying there was ''West Midlands''. The region with the highest number of graduates living there ''5'' years after graduation was ''East of England'' and the region with the least graduates living there was ''West Midlands''.
output.maptext2:
For First degree graduates of all subjects in the Education industry, the region with the highest proportionate increase in graduates who studied there compared to living
                    there 5 years after graduation is South West , where the number of
                    graduates increased by -57.9 %. The region with the largest
                    decrease is Yorkshire and the Humber where the number of graduates decreased by -28.8 %.
